title: Special message in a unique way
text:
A year ago for Christmas I got a morse code bracelet from my teen soon that spelled ‚Äúmama‚Äù, and that touched my heart. I was recently curious to see what other options, words, or messages they had, and I came across this one. It's absolutely perfect!
It has exceeded my expectations greatly as the beads are much bigger than others I've seen. Also to be a one string bracelet, I must say that it feels quite heavy. It is important to point out though that these beads are not as big as most of the ones on ‚Äúprotection healing chakra" bracelets. I personally like the size of these better, not too big, not too small.

The combination of tiger‚Äôs eye beads and hematite ‚Äúdics‚Äù to spell ‚ÄúI love you‚Äù is very creative, and they go very well together. Then there are 5 black obsidian beads on each side which create a contrast, yet they blend in with the spelled message beads. It is well crafted, and the string is strong and very tight. It seems very durable to me.

I feel lucky I am able to ‚Äúreturn the gift‚Äù to my son with this beautiful morse message. The box is pretty enough that you won't need to wrap it, just put a bow on it, and it's ready to gift.

title: Careful not to throw them out with the packaging
text:
I received a package from Amazon today, took out the two items, and threw the box in the trash. Later, I noticed that my earrings were delivered too. I was excited to see them, so I went out to the mailbox, but they weren't there. Eventually I found them under the flap in the cardboard box I'd thrown out. They came in a thin envelope and were almost trashed. Know they come in a thin envelope and be careful not to accidentally throw them out.

The earrings don't undulate as much as I expected from the pictures. I don't know if they were squashed, or if it's just because each pair is unique.

Lastly, I don't know if these are truly hypoallergenic. My ear lobes were itching within about 20 minutes.

I will try again because I love threader earrings. I used to wear them when I was about 12 to 15 and recently I have been wanting a pair and these are my first in many years. Maybe it's just the chain that feels kind of weird.

I wanted to hurry up and post this review today to warn you not to throw them out by mistake, but I will try them again in a few days to see if the earrings caused the itchiness or not. I will ask my sister to try them on too, to see if she has a reaction.

If you don't have sensitive earlobes, these are pretty, fun, and a great value. If you do have sensitive earlobes... then, the jury is still out.

Update: I'm adding a star back on. The second time I wore them, there was no itching, but my ear lobe was sore. The third time, it seems it didn't bother me at all. I will keep testing, but wanted to update to tell you that there was no itching the second time I wore them.

title: Beautiful stone bracelet for yourself or to give!
text:

It has (3) different stones that offers the triple protection, the natural yellow tiger, magnetite, and black onyx. Each stone has its own protection/healing properties which you can read about on its product page.

title: Pretty but confusing
text:
I thought that these earring looked very nice and ordered them, despite not really knowing anything about them. The description is very confusing. The description mentions pearl, crystal, 925 sterling silver and 18K stamped. I believe that these are all incorrect. I believe that the stone is jade and that the metal is possibly gold plated silver. The metal is not stamped, so I do not believe it is 18K gold or 925 sterling silver. Because of the confusing description, I reduced the rating by one star.

I do believe that these earrings are hypoallergenic as I am sensitive to nickel, and have worn them without any problem. They are very pretty and I just love both the metal flower and the green jade stone. I think the design is unusual and very attractive. I do plan to wear these with my green and gold dress, as I think they will look amazing with it.

If you do not care about the inaccurate description, these earrings are a great purchase. They would also make an excellent gift.

text:
[[VIDEOID:6dc099e4d77c0197b9c7b60aabeb3c5a]] The necklace itself it very beautiful and of an abstract enough design that it could be given to virtually any lady who likes a shiny thing. And WOW! does that moissanite SPARKLE! Did you know that moissanite is more sparkly than diamond? It‚Äôs thanks to moissanite‚Äôs ultra-high index of fraction. I used to think that moissanite was a cheap, unsatisfactory diamond alternative, but then I learned that that they have hardness (and therefore durability) comparable to a diamond, so unlike cubic zirconia, you can put them in a daily-wear item and not worry about it showing signs of wear like scratches. After learning about all this and seeing numerous moissanites in person, I‚Äôve decided I like them better than diamonds for their beauty, durability, and affordability. The fact that jewelry moissanites are almost always synthetic is a plus for me too: I hate the thought of slave labor, war financing, and scarring the Earth for the sake of a bauble.

The thing that sets this item apart from other jewelry here on Amazon is the packaging. Not only does the packaging include the documentation for the moissanite and keep it safe in an attractive way (together with a jewelry cleaning cloth I might add), but the wooden box is absolutely over-the-top gorgeous. The highly polished varnish on the wood is absolutely artisan quality and the box feels special and substantial in the hand. It really does an amazing job of being the necklace‚Äôs wingman and making it look incredibly expensive and special. If you really want to give an impressive and memorable gift, but you don‚Äôt have the money to put caviar on the deBeers‚Äôs table, this item is a great choice!

title: medium weight
text:
This 3 layered tiger eye bracelet is really very pretty. For having 3 strings of beads, it's not very heavy.
I do like it but what I don't like is the draw string to tighten it on your wrist. It is definitely a 2 person job to tighten it unless you use your teeth. I was unable to tighten it because the one end became stuck while opening it enough to get my hand and wrist through. I didn't want to pull too hard and break the string.
I will be honest, I'm not model material or any where near that. One model could probably fit into one of my pant legs and still have room to turn around. So yes, my wrist is probably much bigger than an average sized person. In which case, they most likely wouldn't have an issue with opening it to the limit and pulling the string tighter around their wrist. However, a man might have issues since they have bigger hands, well, most do. Anyway, would I recommend this? Yes, to a smaller built person most definitely yes. To a big boned person, yes but with caution.

title: Unique universal adjustable ring
text: I like that this ring is adjustable to be able to fit different fingers. There is a roundish piece that slides within the rectangular top which is how it adjusts. There is a limit to its adjustability but it was a clever way to make it adjustable within the design. Squeezing the ring together makes it smaller and it is very easy to open back to a larger size. I don't know the actual rings largest size, but it fit my middle finger, not my thumb. I have large hands so at a guess I'd say up to size 11. I wore it for several days in a row without removing and it never turned my finger green and held up to regular hand washing. This ring is definitely a universal design for either a man or woman.

title: This is beautiful!
text: This bracelet is so very pretty.  I ordered it for the "healing powers".  Nothing bad has happened and I feel good, so I'm assuming it works.  The weight of the bracelet is a little heavy for my taste, but I only wear during the day so it's fine.  The drawstring closure is easy to use to tighten or loosen as necessary even with one hand.  The gems themselves seem to be high quality without any imperfections and the assembly of the bracelet is top notch!  No gaps between the gems and everything is wrapped tightly so nothing should fall apart. It is completely giftable, but the only thing I wish it had was some little note about what the gemstones do - like their healing properties.  I know, only because I read the description, but if you give it as a gift, the recipient might not know.  I chose this specific bracelet because of what I felt I needed in my life.  I absolutely love this and am so very happy.

title: Beautiful!
text: I had actually never heard of shungite before I came across this listing. That sparked my interest, and I had to learn more. Apparently, shungite is pretty rare and thus more expensive than most stones used for beaded bracelets. There is also a lot of fake shungite out there, so buyer beware. I believe the shungite in this bracelet is authentic due to several quick tests one can do. The bracelet is surprisingly lightweight, which surprised me, but that is supposed to be one of the attributes of shungite. It's also supposed to be antibacterial--how interesting is that? And it has protection qualities. I love the magnetic clasp, and unlike other customers, I've had no issues with mine. Based on my experience, I have to recommend.

title: Not Horrible But Could Use Some Improvement
text:
So I am currently working on slowly switching to more non-toxic and cleaner household products and dish soap was one of the things I needed to work on. I am kind of picky about dish soap because I like to make sure my dishes are spotless and I only clean them by hand. This dish soap caught my eye because I have been wanting to try bar dish soap for a while just didn't know where to start.

First, this dish soap is nicely made. I love the texture and the look of it and how easily you can tell it's handmade. I find the soap soft and easy on my hands without leaving them too dry; however, since it is dish soap I have to consider how well it cleans. This dish soap isn't horrible but it does need some improvements. It was a great degreaser and I noticed it was able to even get off the stubborn grease stains I had but I also noticed it left streaks and marks like it didn't fully clean my dishes the first time. I did re-wash them again with the dish soap just using a sponge instead of my handheld scrubbing brush and it did help a lot more but it does make my glasses and cups kind of milky looking.

Overall, this is a great idea and I don't mind using it. I am hoping there's more improvement on it and I will honestly keep using it either way since I do appreciate that it is cleaner than typical dish soap.

title: Threader earrings are my new faves and these do not disappoint
text:
I really love these earrings. I recently discovered threader earrings and wish it hadn't taken me 48 years to do so. These make a perfect addition to my earring collection. They're really nice quality materials, and feel substantial without feeling heavy. The threader piece glides effortlessly through and hangs behind as though it is part of the overall look (which obviously it is). These are not too long and not too short, and have a lovely twist that sparkles and has *just enough* movement when you're wearing them to make them look super pretty.

I honestly darn near threw them out when they arrived, though, because they're packaged in an envelope that looks suspiciously like some of the postcard marketing materials some shippers toss into boxes. I took a second look just to be sure, and sure enough what I thought was some postcard pitch for a new amazon service/product was actually the earrings. That was close.

These are super giftable if you can find yourself an alternate box to gift them in. Otherwise, the packaging on these doesn't come close to being appropriate for the lovely items inside.

Overall I love these and will wear them as often as I can. Great value, great product, highly recommend.

In my video I show this defect. It‚Äôs not a big deal I can glue it. The lanyard is about 22 inches long and can be shorter to your desired length. It says in the description 19 inches. I measured from the plastic closure to the end of the tassel. I‚Äôm guessing since it‚Äôs handmade the measurements can be a little off. Longer is better for me. The wooden beads are very large (not sure of the millimeter size of them. The lanyard itself is a braided string which makes it strong but I wouldn‚Äôt put anything heavy on it. The tassel doesn‚Äôt go fully around the ring it moves slightly within the space. It also comes with an extra lanyard string plastic closure. I really like this lanyard but it‚Äôs not worth $16. I have a lanyard that has semiprecious gemstones on it and it‚Äôs only $13‚Ä¶now it‚Äôs discount at 20% off which makes it about $10.40 which is a better deal than this one. But to each is own.

title: Gorgeous...but
text: I found these earrings to be stunning when first opened them. The style is right up my alley. They are lightweight and comfortable. But then, there is something not quite right about them. I'm trying to attach photos that depict exactly what I'm talking about, but it's difficult to capture when the finish of the earrings is shiny. I just can't quite capture it. So, I will describe it to the best of my ability. The "rear" of the earring is a thin wire portion that glides through the piercing. The "front" portion is a flattened wire that is wider, blade-like, until the last few millimeters of the earring where it returns to a thin wire. It looks almost as though the earring was designed to have an accent gem or something else on that portion of the wearing. But there's nothing else there. Wire in the back, flattened blade on the front, except where it returns to a thin wire shape at the bottom of the blade. It doesn't look intentional. It appears to be accidental or a modification to a design that was not fully thought out. I hate to say it because the earrings are otherwise perfection. But this oddity took them from FABULOUS to just ok.

title: Classic looking stacking ring
text:
Received this ring today for free as part of the Amazon Vine program for my honest review. The ring arrived packaged by the company in a very cute small, sturdy box, wrapped in a cellophane bag. The ring is exactly as pictured in the images, otherwise I would have added my own photograph to this review, but honestly, it is not needed.
I have always preferred thinner band rings, so stacking rings are perfect for me - not only to stack, but to wear alone as well. This sterling silver ring runs true to size. The design of the ring makes it look as the ring was made from two parts - the first being a completely smooth plain sterling band ring - and the second being a hammered narrower band ring that got attached to the first part. The hammered portion gives off a shine, so from a distance the ring almost looks to be a diamond eternity ring or wedding band, giving the ring a very classic look. Up close, people observing the ring would recognize it is not a diamond band.
It is a great looking ring for the price.
I do wish they would offer rings in half sizes though, so rings stack better overall.

title: Beautiful and unique, but very delicate
text: These earrings are super pretty and very shiny.  I love their unique design, the size is perfect, they're really lightweight, and they don't cause me any discomfort or allergic reaction.  For these reasons, I'm giving them 5 stars.  However, there are some things to consider when deciding whether or not to purchase.  They are VERY delicate and the metal is extremely pliable, which means they can be easily bent and misshapen.  Also, since they simply pull through your piercings, they have no backs or anything to hold them in place.  Therefore, I find myself frequently checking to be sure they are still hanging correctly and not working their way out of my ears. I also find the pull-through design to make them a bit challenging - if not difficult - to put on. It takes me at least a minute or two to get the earring tips lined up with my piercings and then twist and maneuver them into place. These are definitely not "I'm running late so I'll just grab my earrings and put them on in the car while I'm driving" earrings!  If time is limited, I'll wear something else.

title: Stunning Golden Necklace Pendent with Blue Evil Eye
text:
I ordered this Golden Evil Eye Pendent and Chain because the Pendent reminded me of an Egyptian Evil Eye Amulet, I once saw on a Website for a lot of Money. Apparently, Cleopatra wore it for ‚ÄúProtection, Wisdom and Harmony.‚Äù A little like the Cleopatra Amulet, my Evil Eye Pendent has 22 tiny Cubic Zirconia Stones set on it ‚Äì 19 around the Edge and 3 under the Eye. My Pendent feels a little heavy, which gives it a unique, Antique Look and Feel. I have received many Complements on it because it looks very interesting to People. I have worn it since its Arrival; and the Golden Color has not faded away. I really like the Quality of the Pendent as well as the Chain. It‚Äôs made very sturdy because I have slept with it; and it has not ripped off yet. What has really surprised me about this Evil Eye Pendent and Necklace is that the Chain is made of 3 different Sizes of Links. I love the Designer‚Äôs Attention to Detail when they placed 1 particular Size Link between the other 2 Sizes to make sure that the Pendent does not fall off the Chain at all. I opened the Chain and let the Pendent dangle. It was not falling off at all because of that 1 particular Link. That‚Äôs impressive for this Price because I have seen more expensive Pendants fall off and get lost. The Chain is designed to be worn short or longer, ending with a cute Golden Piece that looks like a Pear and a Golden Clasp. The only Thing about this Necklace is the Blue Evil Eye itself, which appears to be made of painted Plastic.
Regarding the colorful Choker: Unfortunately, I was not very impressed with the Choker because it looked and felt cheap in Comparison to the Evil Eye Necklace. The Choker is lightweight, which tells me that the Stones are not real. In Fact, some of the Beads‚Äô Color is coming off, which is why I will deduct 1 Star. I will not be wearing this Choker with my gorgeous Evil Eye Necklace. Overall, I think that the Evil Eye Necklace is a great Value.

title: Amazing Pearls!
text:
I was incredibly impressed with these pearls as soon as I took them out of the box. I‚Äôm a huge fan of baroque pearls because although they capture the same soft and ethereal qualities of round pearls, there‚Äôs just something about them that is more informal, friendlier, natural, authentic, and accessible. Baroque pearls acknowledge that everyone is different and beautiful and worthy of love even if they are not perfect. Now, these pearls are not of consistent quality throughout the necklace. Some of them are extraordinarily luminous while others clearly have some spots where the shell base for the nacre is showing through. Again, this can be seen as a celebration of diversity. All together it is a beautiful necklace and I‚Äôm ever so pleased to have it in my jewelry wardrobe.

Unlike necklaces with smaller baroque pearls, however, this one is living large. the metallic components are bright and shiny with rich 18kt gold color. The size of the pearls is utterly luxurious. Once when I was at the opera, one of the donors who made the performance possible was called onstage and she was a wearing a necklace just like this one. These pearls are a relaxed yet elegant alternative to the stereotypical gumball pearls worn by Southern ladies of a particular socioeconomic status. They are just beautiful and I recommend them highly.

text:

I was concerned about whether they would bend and become misshapen when I put them in my ears. I decided to order the earrings and give them a try, despite my reservations.

I need not have worried. The earrings are quiet strong and are definitely not flimsy. I tried to gently twist them but they held their shape. I did struggle at first to orientate them in order to get them in my ears. I found that looking in a mirror while putting them in helped with that and I soon got the hang of it. They looked great. I wore them all day and they were very comfortable. I was a little worried that they might get tangled in my long hair, but that wasn‚Äôt a problem.

In conclusion, these are an attractive quality unusual pair of earrings, that are well made, retain their shape and are comfortable to wear. What more can you ask of them?

title: Nice earrings!
text: These are pretty earrings! I like the look they create. I love hoop earrings so I knew I would like these too. The reason I took a star away is because I can't get them to stay in my ears right. I put them on before starting dinner, and an hour later checked them, and both were hanging down. I was worried when I ordered them that they would slide down, because french hook earrings do the same thing when I wear them. I have to put those silicone backs on when I wear a pair of french hook earrings. I tried 2 different kinds of silicone backs with these earrings and neither fit. I think the metal width is too wide for them. This would make it really hard to wear these earrings, I am never going to remember to check them every 10 minutes. I tried to do that for a few hours, but I would get busy and forget. When I would check them, they would be hanging down. They never completely fell out, though, so I didn't lose them at least. The CZ stone was a little bigger than I expected, but the size is still okay for me. They did come packaged nicely in a small box. I also thought the price was good for the quality of these earrings. I have very sensitive ears and I can't wear cheap metal earrings. They make my ears itch like crazy within minutes of wearing them. These never irritated my ears, so they are real sterling silver. I really do like them, I just don't know how I'll be able to wear them. It would be nice if the seller included silicone backs that fit these. Maybe I'll be able to figure something out to keep these earrings on right. If I do, I will update this review.

title: Got the Post Location Right
text:
I have a very similar pair of earrings by BreValem which are made in gold-plated silver but the posts were soldered to a dot above the topmost paper clip link, not to the back of it. Somehow that one little flaw all but ruined the design for me. These earrings, though not made with silver, do the right thing for the design by soldering the post to the back of the last clip, which makes the design far more organic. These earrings also have one more link than the BreValem design, but I‚Äôm not sure that I like the new proportions.

I do wish the posts were 925, though. I‚Äôm not sure if you can see it in my photos, but there is a place on the posts where the gold plating thins out and shows the base metal. If I had to guess, the posts were plated with the backs on, which is very irregular. Since I have very sensitive ears, I have to be careful of what metals my earring posts are made of, so I am a little leery of these. The gold color on the chains is bright, but the plating is not polished to a very bright shine.

The pearls are fair quality. Both of mine had a ring around the midsection of the pearls where the nacre was thin and so the lustre was dull. The BreValem pearls were slightly bigger and higher quality. Currently the BreValem earrings cost $25 and these cost about $14.

If all you need is the look, these earrings are a good choice, but if you need to be sure that the earrings will be safe for sensitive ears, hold up to close scrutiny, and have some inherent material value, you may wish to consider another pair.

title: Needs Quality Control
text:
I love the design and storage capacity of this bag, however I‚Äôm very disappointed with the damage it arrived with (see photos)

This arrived wrapped in plastic, which the buckles had broken through. When I removed it the first thing I noticed was the right-side buckle, which hadn‚Äôt been properly aligned to its magnetic closure and appears lopsided when the bag is closed. The same buckle‚Äôs leather is also noticeably damaged where it wraps around the metal buckle, it almost looks as though it was repurposed from a used item. Strange since the right-side buckle does not have any of the same issues, it was properly aligned and has no raw edges.

There is no need to unbuckle the bag to access the interior, if you lift the buckles it opens using only the magnetic closures. The interior is lined with a green material that feels similar to jute; the color is not what is advertised, but since it isn‚Äôt visible I‚Äôm not bothered by it. The woven texture is already pilling, however, and if keys or something similar were to scrape against the side the lining would be easily damaged, I‚Äôm not holding out much hope for its longevity.

The front of the bag has a long scrape down the entire length, and when turned over there are also indentations on the back. It seems when stored they were packed too tightly against each other which left damage on both sides of the bag. While I love the look of worn/vintage leather, that isn‚Äôt the effect these marks give.

I was really excited to receive this bag, and am so sad that I can‚Äôt recommend it. There is a clear lack of quality control in the production and, since it was shipped in clear plastic as its only protector, the manufacturers seem to have had every opportunity to inspect and remove this particular item and chose not to.

title: Enjoyable Music Box Sounds Best with Lid Open
text:
I find this to be an adorable mini music box with well executed detailed carvings on the exterior, as well as some colorful floral stickers on the inside top lid with words that read ‚ÄúYou are my Sunshine‚Äù. This matches the name of the well-known song back from the 1900‚Äôs that dreamily plays when you hand crank the handle. There is a notable perimeter of dried glue around the inside edges, corners, and centerpiece, which I didn't anticipate. I usually enjoy the music box tunes, which often remind me of chimes. When I first played this sunflower music box, I could not recognize this song that I know -- until I cranked the handle at a higher speed.

I also noticed the higher pitched notes (right hand if this were a keyboard) sound perfectly in tune and lovely. However, I find myself distracted by the lower pitched notes (left hand if this were a keyboard), which did not sound harmonious with the higher notes (lid closed). Yet, I learned that the heavily competitive lower notes became quieter with an open lid. Overall, this small music box is charming and attractive, while offering an enchanting rendition of an older popular song.

text:
So dainty, simple,, beautifully designed, these dangle earrings are all that is being described on the site. And yes, what you see is what you get, just as they say. They look SO elegant, and very delicate.

I wasn‚Äôt sure about the use of the little silicone backs as they come in a separate baggie. I can‚Äôt really see them in the model‚Äôs photos or video. I assumed they are meant to be pushed half way up to the hind of the lobe, so the earrings stay put, but I wasn‚Äôt able to get them through. READ THIS PART and BE CAREFUL: On my intent to push one through, I bent it, and now it‚Äôs a bit distorted, so sad :‚Äô-( I hope they don‚Äôt come off while wearing them. If they are needed, Metzakka needs to provide ones with a bigger hole. It doesn't seem right that they are meant to stay a the tip of the back [see pics].

I must add that I appreciate the beautiful and very useful jewelry box, great for traveling and for avoiding them from bumping around and with each other.

title: Very Flexible but Fragile
text:
I think this is a delicate, exquisite necklace called jade jewelry, featuring three 6 mm emerald green beads associated with the heart chakra. It is labeled sterling silver and has the most unusual centering capability that I recall ever witnessing. In addition to the very flexible extender length, the centering of the three beads is quite adjustable, as well.

Most often, I have seen stationary necklace focal points that become off center, if one tries to shorten the length to a choker form. With this item, the key is to keep moving all the silver balls along the wispy silver chain, until satisfied. This includes the two silver balls on each side of the green beads, as well as the silver ball at the end of the chain.

A main challenge for me was operating the spring clasp with a narrow opening, along with how to secure the prominent pointed end of the loose chain. Without clear instructions, my necklace easily got jammed up and temporarily knotted. I hate knots in chains, so I ended up trying to let my medium length hair or clothing cover the loose draping chain end, anyways. This is very giftable with a lovely presentation, thank you note, and care tips.

title: Flat screw back is incredibly comfortable!
text:
This is a review of: Flat Screw Back CZ Cartilage Earrings for Women,Small CZ Flat Back Cubic Zirconia Stud Earrings Silver Helix Earrings CZ Studs Hypoallergenic Steel Jewelry Gift for Girls,Toddlers(4mm CZ, Silver)

I have been planning to try flat-backed earrings for a while, and these delicate, shiny, inexpensive earrings got me to pull the trigger. I have a cartilage piercing that I rarely wear earrings in, because the sharp earring backs irritate the skin behind my ear. I popped one of these earrings in and I honestly could sleep in it. There is no irritation at all. The earring itself is nicely constructed. It's simple, but elegant. The earring set comes with 2 extra backs because they know me apparently. The whole thing comes in a black pleather snap-close pouch, that is a nice touch, but a little unnecessary. Overall, I love it. I will get more!

However, I usually have very sensitive ears, and these have not bothered me after several days now, so I think I'm in the clear. I love these earrings!

title: Very lightweight and comfortable to wear at length

These are cute shiny silver earrings that are great for casual wear or going out. They are very lightweight so you can wear them at length and forget you have them on. Since they twist into your ear, it takes a few seconds of turning them just so, to fit into your ears properly, and there is no backing, the shape of the earrings is supposed to keep them in place. But you may want to add a rubber backing just in case.

These are very delicate and you have to be careful not to bend them or alter their shape when putting them on. It's helpful to use a mirror to help guide them into your ears easily.

*My ears can be sensitive to some earrings and noticed that one of my ears started to feel itchy after wearing them for a little while, so something to consider if you have sensitive ears as well.

title: Useful Size and Inspirational
text:
[[VIDEOID:279e574c0b1cd0e2edd3b4c7469e4199]] This appears to be a great small scale 9.5‚Äù x 6.3‚Äù canvas zippered bag, adorned with a passionate expression in big, black capital letters. It is compact enough to grab and go -- yet also roomy and spacious enough, with a width of about 2‚Äù, to carry multiple items. The brass zipper appears a light golden color and attractive, yet my zipper arrived a little sticky, too. I found it helpful to rub a bit of soap, along the zipper.

The wrist loop is terrific for carrying and handling. However, even though I am small-boned, I have to take extra time to get my hand through the loop. I am a bit taller than average height, and my knuckles are somewhat larger. The loop size may be possibly a distraction, if someone were to have a larger hand than mine.

An off-white canvas color is appealing and clean currently, but my expectations are that the white may not last very long. It doesn‚Äôt take much for dirt and smudges to potentially show up on white, which may necessitate more frequent washes. The lovely black letters could possibly start to degrade after multiple washes, yet it is too early to tell right now. If you need something good-sized and meaningful, this could be a helpful, earthy, inspiring bag to have around.

title: White Gold Plating May Not Be Hypoallergenic
text:
The Pinky Promise Ring is a sentimental idea that I initially loved. Lately, I have been wanting to find .925 sterling silver, nickel-free, hypoallergenic jewelry. I was happy that this ring was listed as hypoallergenic, adjustable to sizes 6 ‚Äì 9, and would arrive with a jewelry polishing cloth.

However, it turned out that the ring appeared flimsy, in person, and potentially allergenic to me. Adjusting it down a size or two left a huge edge jutting out (tried to show on photos). I was not sure what justified such a price, at this point, after also struggling a while with a knife, to open this very tight, taped up jewelry box.

I had an allergic skin reaction after wearing this ring. I realized how much confusion I had from inconsistencies in the online product description. This pinkie ring was listed as 100% sterling silver, lead-free, and nickel-free, in some areas vs. white gold plated with no karat listed, in other areas, irregularly. I do not recall having prior experience with white gold plating before.

I learned later that white gold is usually an alloy, which includes some nickel and zinc, etc. I felt dispirited but learned to be even more cautious around the surface plating of rings and reading descriptions very carefully. I perceive that skin only touches the surface plating (described as white gold at this point), until the plating wears off. Those who do not suffer from allergies may really like a touching, sentimental ring package, such as this.

title: Nicely made, mid-size leather purse with custom look and features!
text:
I was attracted to this purse for several reasons. The leather material has an authentic ‚Äúraw‚Äù look, feel, and aroma. To access the main section, you have to use two buckle straps with magnetic snap closures. Personally, it‚Äôs a little unwieldy to have to release two straps rather than one when I need to get inside quickly, but the bag‚Äôs classic design offsets this minor inconvenience.

The main section of the bag and pockets are lined with a lime green material ‚Äì the color wouldn‚Äôt have been my first choice, but it does provide protection for the back side of the hide.

The interior has two leather-trimmed dividers and a side zipper pocket. While the main section of the purse is a bit narrow (3‚Äù wide when fully extended), you could fit a tablet, eReader, and/or cell phone inside.

The front has an open pocket measuring 8-1/2‚Äù wide x 6-1/2‚Äùhigh x 1-1/2‚Äù deep. Good place for a small notepad, ID wallet, keys, pens, etc. The rear of the bag has a single, zippered pocket for small, thin items.

An adjustable, detachable strap gives you the option of carrying the purse over the shoulder or cross-body. The strap is on the long side, with 5 holes to adjust for height and how you prefer to carry it.

Overall, the bag has great visual appeal. I wish it were a bit deeper, easier to open, and had a more neutral color interior lining. However, none of these things would keep me from buying it or giving it as a nice gift.

title: Beautiful and unique, but difficult to put on
text:
These earrings arrived in a hand-pressed paper envelope embedded with pressed flowers and tied with a beaded cord. Very cute presentation and suitable for gifting. The earrings themselves are super pretty and very shiny. I love their unique design, the size is great, they're really lightweight, and they don't cause me any discomfort or allergic reaction. For these reasons, I'm giving them 5 stars. However, I did experience some issues with these earrings, which may or may not be specific to me.

First of all, these earrings are VERY difficult to put on. I really like the "threader" concept, but WOW. They are definitely not a good option when I'm limited on time - or patience. The most challenging part is just getting the wire tips lined up with my piercings. If I can get past this step (I'm not always successful), then it's not too hard to twist and maneuver them into place. Maybe the level of challenge depends on how far your piercings are from the bottom of your ear lobe, and perhaps this isn't as difficult for others as it is for me, but there have been times when I've finally just given up after several minutes of struggling and opted for a simple wire dangle instead (then had a little sip of the mommy juice for my troubles)!

Another consideration is that these earrings have no backs or anything to hold them in place. Therefore, I'm frequently checking to be sure they are still hanging correctly and not working their way out of my ears. If I'm wearing a turtleneck top, I find that the bottom of the earrings hits the top of my shirt/sweater and starts pushing them up and out of my ears.

These are nice earrings, but they may not be the best choice for everyone.

title: Very delicate and pretty
text:
I was excited for this necklace with the 3 amethyst (my birthstone) to wear something nice but not too much on my days off. This was listed as a chain that adjusted from 16" to 18". Honestly, that's a very tight 18", so I won't be able to wear it myself. The chain is so delicate (and lovely!) that if I were to try wearing it at the very end link in the clasp, it wouldn't take much for the strain to cause it to give way.

It's a lovely gift for a younger person, though, like a teen or preteen. I'll be giving this to one of my daughters, who I know will love to wear it on special days. The amethyst stones are clear and natural, polished and a perfect purple shade.

It's a beautiful and inexpensive gift, but just not really of a length for most adults to wear comfortably.

title: Perfect For That Deer Person
text:
Chances are if you are looking at this listing, you feel some relationship to deer, whether that is from staring at your dad's bottle of Teacher's Highland Cream or reading about Harry Potter's patronas, or waiting all year to watch Rudolph again, you feel some kind of connection with them. I get it, and just knowing these are in my ears makes me feel good. The jade stone adds vibrancy to the design, making them even more satisfying. I know it sounds crazy, but if deer are your spirit animal, you get it. And yes, these are very comfortable and easy to wear, and come with both metal and rubber backs, though both are quite small, and you might like to replace them with larger ones, if you have a bounty of them, like I do. The small ones the earrings came with are sufficient, but for me, larger backs make me feel a little more confident that the earrings are not going to shift or get pulled off easily, when adjusting your hair around or changing togs or taking off a jacket. It is not a big deal, but being an earring back connoisseur of sorts, I did want to mention it.

By the way, these beautiful earrings come in a dark blue velvet box, which makes them all the more terrific. If you know a deer person, this would be a fantastic and unusual gift. I love them and highly recommend them. Really beautiful..

title: High Quality, Handmade Floral Embossed Beautiful Wallet
text: [[VIDEOID:ae12291e7549e1f34720ebcf7c494ed9]] This is definitely a high quality, handmade leather wallet! The leather itself is soft and sturdy. The floral embossing is impeccable and really compliments the overall design. I love that there's a zippered compartment inside for change and loose items. I'm able to fit my necessities as well as some extras, like a silk hankie! This fits well in my hand, and I love the wrist strap. If I had one singular criticism it would be that I would've liked the strap to be constructed of more than a single layer of leather, although this certainly isn't a deal breaker. You can tell that this wallet was made with care and detail in mind. Even the wrist strap is embossed, which is a nice touch. I really appreciated the included drawstring dust bag with little wooden beads on the ties. The magnet closure is perfectly functional. I love grabbing this out of my purse while running into the store or gas station quickly, as well as taking it on longer excursions where I don't want to carry a purse but still need to tote my little treasures and credit cards. This is a totally solid wallet. I know that it will last me for the rest of my days, and I plan to rock it for just as long! I highly recommend this floral leather beauty!

title: Rugged
text: This Toros Craft Crossbody leather wallet has a very rugged, western appearance. My first thought upon receiving it was that this should be a holster, not a crossbody, and I wonder why the makers didn't find a way to make this an option. However, as a crossbody, it has a good strong strap with nice brass-like clips, making it very secure to be carried in that manner.  It is sized to fit larger phones; I think a small phone would fall too deeply into it to be easily retrieved. It accommodates my 6.5 inch Z Fold nicely. Most wallets have a soft microfiber lining for the phone's screen; this doesn't. I'm guessing the soft calfskin doesn't pose any risk. Whereas most phone wallets have a magnet closure, this one has an old fashioned snap closure. I don't know if that's a +or - feature.

title: Potent natural ingredients
text: I ordered the Timeless face salve for aging skin. The scent is unique and pleasant. The two things that jump out for me was It definitely smells like a natural product. Not all overly sweet like other creams. And it's really not a cream. It is a solid that melts as it is warmed by rubbing. I would have liked a spatula type utensil to keep the salve clean from being dipped in with my hands but that's just my preference and I'm sure they are keeping it less wasteful for the environment. Which is good. I also love that it is made in the US with natural ingredients and is a woman owned business. The salve is very potent. You only need a little and it goes a long way. Softens skin well. Does feel a bit tacky on skin but does eventually soak in. I only use at night before bed for that reason. I have also started using it on my fingers and cuticles and it is doing wonders.

title: Vibrant and Fun
text:
I got this set of posters as a gift for my 14-year-old daughter, to put up in her bedroom. She really likes bright, colorful, positive messaging. She's had them up for a few weeks, and she is happy with them.

The posters are delivered rolled up, in great condition. They unroll without any creasing, and within a couple of hours are laying flat and ready to be hung.

The colors in the posters are exactly as seen in the product description. They actually look even more lively and fun in person (in my opinion). The poster material is sturdy, with great lamination quality. The images are clear and viewable from across a large room. With some lighting on them, they come to life even more.

The concept really works. Not only are the colors really vibrant, but the "Angel" titles at the top are quite pleasing, and each poster draws your attention to the positive message. It's all just done tastefully, with a great combination of color, design, text, and white space.

This is a great set of attractive posters. I highly recommend them.

title: Expensive Piece of Low Quality Jewelry For The Price
text:
A rather simple piece of jewelry that is overpriced for its‚Äô low to average quality. It is advertised as 925 sterling silver topped with rose gold plating.

925 sterling silver is of average quality, and when companies don‚Äôt state the grade or karat of the gold plating, you can safely assume the gold karat is probably only 10Karat gold plating which again is the lowest quality of gold plating.

At almost $50 you are overpaying for a rather simple plain piece of jewelry that is overpriced for its average quality of 925 sterling silver and of low quality gold plating.

More likely than not, this piece of jewelry will tarnish quickly against the skin and possibly turn greenish.

title: Compact natural leather crossbody purse for special occasions or everyday use!
text:
This natural leather handmade purse makes a great first impression! The front accent piece is trim-stitched, as are the front sides and rear of the bag.

The flap closes with a magnetic snap. Inside is a center zipper pocket and five slip pockets ‚Äì four of them hold ID or credit cards, and one is a longer opening. This provides a lot of organization for the essentials.

The detachable, adjustable crossbody strap clips to gold-tone rings on the sides of the purse. I noticed a little color variation in the strap, but I guess that‚Äôs the nature of leather.

The purse is very pretty, and while it‚Äôs a bit on the small side, it‚Äôs perfect when you only need to take the basics. It comes with a burlap cloth bag for storage.

I appreciate the quality of handmade items, and this purse offers the look and feel of high-end, top-quality leather and craftsmanship while providing a lot of organization for the basic essentials. Highly recommended for personal use or it makes a great gift for someone special!

title: Smells great AND feels great!
text:
This IS for your face, I assumed it would be a cream or a serum, but it is definitely a salve. I‚Äôve never used a salve for my face before so I was a little hesitant and unsure at first. I also wasn‚Äôt sure which ‚Äúskin type‚Äù formula to select, so I ordered the ‚Äútimeless‚Äú formula. (I didn‚Äôt know this at the time of ordering, but their direct website has a quiz to help you determine which formula type to use).

Since it is a salve, I found the easiest way to apply this product was to rub my fingertips in a circular motion to get the amount of product desired, then apply directly to the face. The directions say to apply a thin coat, but my face must‚Äôve been extra dry because it soaked it right up, so I needed to apply another layer! My skin felt so soft, and moisturized! I used it all over my face, including underneath my eyes. This formula has a wonderful, refreshing smell, and I love it so much! I put this on before bedtime, and it was a nice soothing scent to fall asleep to. I definitely want to try other formulas!

After using the product, I was so happy
and impressed, I decided to visit their website. I discovered that you can take a little online quiz to help you determine which ‚Äúskin type‚Äù formula to order. Remember how I mentioned I wanted to try other formulas? Well, now I know which ones I want to add to my ‚Äútimeless‚Äú formula regimen. Yay!

I was also impressed to learn that this company is highly devoted to using all natural ingredients as well as biodegradable packaging.

I love the smell and I love how it feels on my skin; two things I never thought I would say about a salve for the face!

title: Artistic and you need a whole set!
text:
The woodgrain parts covered in resin are spectacular enough, you can see the grain and it's 2 different 1/3ds so you gte contrast along with the grain. They easily appear to hold up to nearly anything so they'd make fantastic coasters for any purpose or occasion!

Now the killer piece is the Blue Emerald. Simply... gorgeous. Translucent, patterned, striations in parts and mine had half the underside of that section with swirly, near diamond plate like you see in elevators as a pattern in that goreous blue. Silky smooth to the touch from the whole thing and you can see and feel the hand-shaved and sanded edges as well. Just a superb piece of work and had personalized notes inside from those who made these come to life!

title: Black Opal is indeed colorful; look carefully at the descriptions
text:
I thought the colors shown in the photo for the black opal were due to reflections, but the colors are an intrinsic part of the "opal" and the photos are spot on. I should have checked out the details and the heading more carefully - for some reason I was expecting something larger and bolder. The eye-catching intricacies of the silver setting at real-size are not nearly as noticeable as they appear in the photos. Nevertheless, this is a versatile piece and can be worn with many different colored outfits. The rolled silver chain is beautiful and well crafted.

When deciding on a stone, look carefully at the descriptions - the opals are all "lab-created" while the remaining two are the real deal. When I selected the black opal, I assumed that "lab-created" was being used in the way that cubic zirconia and other gemstones are created in laboratories, closely resembling actual gemstones. My black opal has a disappointingly plastic feel to it and I wonder whether "lab-created" is a euphemism for plastic. In fact it is the silver portions of this jewelry piece (the setting and the chain) that rescue it.

title: Thoughtful gift for someone you appreciate

She said this is a unique bracelet that she can wear everyday and think of how much I appreciate her. It has a decent weight to it, relatively stretchy but not to an extreme. I'm not sure what the going price for lava rock jewelry is but I think its a little high for non-formal bracelet. Gift box is amazingly impressive, really doesn't need wrapping at all.

title: So encouraging and beautiful!
text:
Here is a beautiful and encouraging bracelet!

Made by Waymaker Leather, the Strength bracelet comes in a brown logo'd box (featuring a very neat lion and lamb), inside a drawstring cream-colored linen bag. On the inside of the box is the Bible verse Joshua 1:9, the one which goes with the Strength bracelet. The same verse is laser-engraved on a thin brown leather bracelet with a silver metal buckle.

The bracelet is made for men, and I'm a woman, so the bracelet was quite a bit too long for me. But the Waymaker shop owner and creator, Torrie, included a note with the bracelet with instructions on how to shorten the bracelet. I just had to snip off several inches, and it was perfect.

The end of the leather bracelet tucks into the back of the buckle. That keeps it very safe and secure while you're wearing it.

I *love* this bracelet. It's so beautiful, and the Bible verse is so meaningful to me. What a wonderful gift.

title: Until the bracelet broke my teen had rated this Valentine's gift 5 *s
text:
UPDATE: Unfortunately, the bracelet broke over the weekend of 02/24/2023 the rattail cording snapped, and my teen lost 5 of the 6 beads that were released when the bracelet broke. Of course, my teenager was upset because it was a gift, at least nothing happened to the necklace.

ORIGINAL REVIEW: The Temoto Triple Protection Amethyst, Obsidian, and Hematite Bracelet made a great Valentine's Day gift for my teenage rockhound. The real gemstones are very heavy, but the two rows of beads on this handmade bracelet are woven together in a crisscross pattern with rat tail cording; giving the bracelet strength and stability. The macrame slide knot has a beautiful, stainless steel tree of life bead in the center giving the bracelet a unique look.
The necklace with its large Dream Amethyst focal bead was a nice addition to this gift, this was a lovely and unique gift that my teenager was ready to this gift off show off to their other rockhound and gem-collecting friends.

The Bottom Line: You will not find such a beautiful handmade bracelet for $20.99, Temoto's handwork on this Amethyst, Obsidian, and Hematite Bracelet is worth much more. For real semi-precious gems, this bracelet is a beautiful bargain and highly giftable.

title: Really cute decor pieces, but has errors!
text:
These decor pieces are really nice looking and they look lovely on the wall. It's a four piece set that you can use together or spread in different areas. The boards aren't too thick, nor too thin. They have little flappy hinges on each board to hang these on a picture nail, so the damage to a wall is minimal.

The major issue for me is the missing punctuation and missing words on two plaques. The first one that says "This is us" has words underneath that says, "Our life. Our story. Our home" It's missing the period after home, which really bothers me. The other one says, "Bless this" then underneath it says, "And all who enter". It's missing the word 'home' which is a HUGE error! I feel if a company is going to make beautifully decorated decor items, they would at least check their grammatical issues. These errors stick out like a sore thumb and is rather aggravating.

Overall, these are beautiful plaques and they would look beautiful on the wall. Due to the missing punctuation and word, I don't think I can keep these on my wall. I really hope the company fixes these errors so I can get another set because they're beautiful, well-made, and would look lovely in my living room. If these two errors don't bother you, then these will be worth buying. If errors bother you, like they do me, I don't suggest buying these decor pieces. I guess it all comes down to your personal preference.

text:
[[VIDEOID:238e67f2345881f708e3c10b2f11b9d5]] This is a very beautiful and well made bracelet. The combination of stones together look great and they are held together tightly. If well cared for this bracelet should last a very long time.

It comes with a card listing the name and explaining the known effects/uses of each type of stone. The stones included are:

Amethyst
Rose Quartz
Chalcedony
Turquoise
Citrine
Tiger's Eye
Agate

This could be a great gift for a child, teen, or adult. It has a very large size range to accommodate very large to very small wrists. I have a pretty small wrist measuring about 6.5 inches and based on the measurements provided in the listing I didn't think it would adjust that small but it absolutely does and even smaller. At its smallest adjustment the inner diameter of the bracelet is about 5¬æ inches. At its largest adjustment it has an inner diameter of about 10¬º inches. So it will adjust to fit almost any wrist.

I love this bracelet and I plan on wearing it a lot so if there are any issues in the future I will update this review but right now it seems fantastic. It's well made and beautiful. It really would make a great Easter gift or a gift for any occasion. I highly recommend it and will probably be buying another one for my 12 yr old daughter because she also loves it.

I hope this was helpful.

title: Design is nice, and it looks pretty when worn, but the quality of the turquoise stone is a concern!
text:
I ordered this ‚Äúadjustable size‚Äù ring in Sterling Silver with a Turquoise stone. When I opened the nice presentation box, I found the stone was dull and dark ‚Äì nothing like the photo in the item‚Äôs listing. I had to take it out into the sunlight to see the color and detail in the stone.

Most jewelry is stamped with either a maker‚Äôs mark or to indicate the type/purity of the metal. In this case, the ‚Äú925‚Äù should be readable. The ring has a few depressions on the back of the stone‚Äôs setting, but nothing is clear or legible.

I measured the ring and it‚Äôs a Size 8. My attempt to make the band a little smaller changed the shape into an oval, so if you need to resize the ring to fit, it may be best to take it to a jeweler who can maintain the circular shape.

The detail in the feather pattern is strong and well-finished. Overall, the design is very nice, and it looks pretty when worn, but the quality of the stone and the verification stamp of the silver setting are lacking. For me, the price is a bit too high for the product.

title: Oh, these are STUNNING. I am speechless.
text:
I've never owned black pearls largely because I've never been interested in black pearls but WOW have I been missing out. I have dark hair so always just kind of assumed they'd blend in and disappear, but no - these are absolutely gorgeous. The sheen of them is so much more beautiful than in the photos - subtle purple, blue, turquoise hues in the light. The quality is fantastic and the pearls are virtually identical so no worries about mismatching sizes etc. The sterling silver did not cause me any irritation (I have a nickel allergy) and they held up well. I wore these on a work trip and my coworker begged me to borrow them. I have a LOT of pearl earrings in a LOT of colors and styles but these simple black pearls skyrocketed to the top of my favorites without an ounce of competition. I simply love them and cannot recommend them enough.

I did see someone mention that they're small - I'm confused because I tend to like my earrings, especially pearls and studs in general, to be on the large side, and I thought the size of these was fine. They're not what I would call LARGE pearls but I think they would look gaudy if they were much larger and they certainly aren't small - based on my other earrings in my collection for comparison, they're 9mm as described. Not a single complaint from me.

title: Attention to detail- quality made.. a few caveats to think of..
text:
Straightforward, embroidery floss bracelet with attention to detail and quality finish. Nothing bulky- it is tightly bound on x2 thinner silk strands of floss.. knotted ends keep from fraying or fly away ends and evenly placed knots fall on each side to hold tiny pendant in place, upright and centered.

Slip knot clasp offers ability to put on/adjust using one hand which is ideal! One size will fit adult or child by simple tightening or loosening of pull strings. Designed unisex the center heart shape bead may not be perceived by all as such! Tbh, ours was gifted to 19yr old boy from 3yr bff nephew- and he loves to wear 24/7 because of meaning to him. But something to keep in mind for recipient.

The handmade feature elevates the effort/thoughtfulness of any gift..
I wish that was made known to the recipient when gifting. Including that fact on the tag or insert card- it‚Äôs a great feature to let it be known. Note to seller! For price point being higher.. I feel using a sterling silver metal center bead- one that would not tarnish or fade would be best. A small increase in cost to make but would justify price being more acceptable- well, creating longevity for wearing!

Overall, very nicely crafted bracelet- sold at higher price point than most- only reason for 4 star. Hoping info helps decision- stay safe everyone!

title: *I just LOVE this cute pyramid set!!* :) So handy & such colorful little pyramids!
text:
I got the set of 4 pyramids for "Mental Wellness, Good Luck, & Prosperity" & I just love my wee little pyramids!! I think they're so cute & beautiful! I've been wanting a crystal pyramid for awhile now, but usually they're quite large & expensive, so I like how this is a nice, affordable set of multiple small pyramids! They're vibrantly colored & well made and the matching necklace/pendant they come with is a cool addition to the set! I like how you can even take the pendant off of the necklace cord if you wish to put the pendant on a different necklace (you just move the gold thread piece upwards that's on the cord & then you can remove the necklace cord from the pendant.)

Everything comes packaged neatly & safely in a pretty, re-usable gift box where the lid of it opens & snaps shut magnetically/securely, which is quite a nice added touch! It comes with a card with some useful crystal information on it that explains how to "charge" your crystals/pyramids, & it lists some of their Orgonite crystals that are common/popular crystals that are good for starting off with for some basic, common uses. There's a neat wooden pendant included in the set as well, if you wish to use it as a pendant or you can place it under one of your pyramids, or hang it up somewhere as an ornament/decoration. There's also a black velvet bag for the pendant necklace.

The seller also includes a card with their contact information if you have any issues with the product, questions, etc & wish to contact them. On the back of that card, you can scan the code that's on it for a free e-book entitled "7 Crystals to Balance Your Chakras."

I personally think it's a lovely set for personal use or to give as a gift set to someone that has a nice variety of cute, little crystal pyramids...especially if you don't like the look of having large crystal pyramids sitting around your home, or don't have much extra table space to place them. These small ones blend in well in a home & can fit most anywhere & are lovely, brightly-colored, attractive, eye-catching little beauties in my opinion! :)

title: Lovely and encouraging
text:
I've loved malachite since I first saw it when I was a little girl. So, I found this necklace exceptionally beautiful first for the gems/beading. The three beads have a nice weight to them and the striping on each of them is different, as are the exact colors. Golden angel wings connect the beads to the necklace itself, which is a dainty chain link with an extender chain (that you connect the lobster clasp to). The weight of the beads helps the necklace/pendant hang nicely, plus it's very comfortable (not too heavy).

I did find the clasp to be a bit difficult to attach to the extender chain. Of course, I'm trying to do this behind my own back (ha ha) so I can't see the chain, but normally I haven't found this to be difficult. (You know. After a few years of wearing jewelry working the clasps becomes second nature.) With this, it took me, at first, 3 attempts to get the clasp actually on a link instead of sliding around on the chain; another time it took 5 attempts! Although at least both times I did finally get it right.

The best thing about this necklace is the personal encouragement it gives me. I'm not so much someone who buys a gem for its particular meaning, but for its beauty to me. So I do love this for the beautiful green malachite. Even more meaningful, perhaps, is the necklace's overall design along with the angel wings. It reminds me very much of my faith, and in particular a Bible chapter in the Psalms, number 91. Such a lovely visual reminder!

title: Fine Value for the Money
text:
I like that this necklace features a beautiful, sparkly CZ. Heart-cut CZ tend to fall into two camps: Dull and lifeless cuts that have too few facets to reflect light and sparkle or too many facets that create a gem that looks like it‚Äôs trying too hard. The CZ in this necklace hits a perfect middle ground: Enough facets to sparkle in a lovely way, but unapologetic.

I selected this necklace because it reminds me of the charming diamond heart necklace that Elizabeth Taylor wears in Cat on a Hot Tin Roof. However, I wish the chain were one of the sliding adjustable ones or had one smaller catch link. On the smallest catch link it doesn‚Äôt quite come up to choker length, which would be the best length for this necklace. Speaking of the extender, it has a somewhat unfinished look since there isn‚Äôt a bead or charm at the end of it. That is consistent with the price, however.

What worries me about this necklace is that it‚Äôs not a real bezel-set necklace. Instead, the CZ appears to be glued into the setting. Again, it‚Äôs to be expected at the current price point of about $14. Bezel settings are time-consuming to make and therefore expensive to offer. This necklace gives the impression of a bezel setting at a lower price point.

Thankfully, the culet of the heart cut CZ does not poke out the back of the pendant. I have seen this issue numerous times with heart-cut gems since heart-cut gems tend to be slightly deeper than brilliants. That this necklace avoids any inadvertent scratches is a good thing.

This would be a lovely gift for a charming young person or the perfect finishing touch for someone who wants to dress up as Elizabeth Taylor for Halloween. With proper care it should last quite a while, but one should probably not wear it while showering, swimming, or hard exercise. I can‚Äôt tell what kind of glue is holding the gem in, but seeping water and hard wear can break even the best bonds over time. I recommend this necklace as a good value for the price point.

title: The Chain and Setting for the Stone are Nice
text: The rope chain (marked 925) for this necklace is very nice. I also like the setting for the turquoise stone although I wish the back was closed. The stone is not a faceted stone and there is no need for the back to be open. Something that gave me pause is the bale fastened onto the stone's setting to accommodate the chain. It do appear to be finished on the edges and the surface is neither shiny nor patinaed. It does say silver 925 on it but it is very worn down. The other thing is, there is a small round hole drilled into the top of the bale that doesn't seem to serve a purpose. It's just there. It just seems like this "bale" may have been created for another use and ended up being used as the bale in this jewelry piece. I have no idea about the turquoise... but I have never seen real turquoise polished to a high shine, as this piece is. All the turquoise I own has a soft, sort of matte, smooth finish, but no real shine. So I can't comment on its authenticity. But for the price, my feelings are mixed on weather my necklace is all sterling silver and turquoise, hence the 3 star rating.

title: Heavy duty, beautiful handmade leather handbag!
text: This is a beautiful handmade bag/satchel/purse, crafted in India of goat leather.  As stated, it  measures 11x9x2.5 inches.  There are two buckles on the front which have magnetic metal snaps for closure.  There is a zippered compartment on the backside and a large slip in pocket on the front, under the flap and buckle closures.  Inside the purse, are two large slip in pockets (like purse dividers) and a large zippered compartment spanning the width of the purse.  The inside of my purse is a green colored canvas material.  I think the stitching is superb.  The adjustable shoulder strap is longer than 4 feet., close to 4.5ft.  It has excellent quality thick metal carabiners on the ends to attach to the D-rings on the sides of the satchel, and has a buckle to attach in the middle to adjust the length of the strap, so you can use as cross body, shoulder bag or underarm.  It feels like a saddlebag, - although being stiff and of thick leather, it is quite bendable and easily accessible.  I received a nice note inside the bag, explaining some of the qualities of the satchel, the handmade process and the progression of the leather softening and it taking on a leather patina as it ages.  I think it will look great with jeans.  I believe it's a great price for the quality, should last a long time and I would highly recommend.  It would make a great gift.

title: Lovely handmade bag, untraditional, great hand-craftsmanship!
text:
This arrives well packaged in a fold-top acetate bag.
If giving as a gift, this is challenging to wrap as it arrives. I suggest finding an appropriately sized box to wrap it in or use a standard sized gift bag. This is a nice *almost* standalone any occasion gift for any purse using gal or murse using guy as it is neither overtly feminine nor masculine. The reason I say '*almost* standalone gift' is that I was raised to never gift a purse &/or wallet without including 2 cents or more (I usually include a dollar) - I think (if I remember right) this is a superstition that giving an empty purse/wallet is wishing the recipient to always be broke & including some kind of money is wishing the recipient financial abundance. Do with that what you will.
I loved the note tucked inside the purse from the crafter. While it was printed/typed, it had the heartfelt wording of a handwritten note & was very nice.
The workmanship is wonderful. No loose seams/threads, obvious attention to detail, quality construction. You can tell the crafter cares about & enjoys their craft!
It has a wonderful coloration & smells great (I love the smell of leather)! While the included note suggests that using the purse will give it a patina & dissipate the smell, I've always used a quality (& time tested company) leather protectant & this is no exception. I like the coloration that it currently is & want to keep it this way. The 'leather smell' WILL dissipate with time no matter what.
The outside back of this purse has a medium-small zippered pocket & the front has a large (mainly open) pocket. Though this pocket does have a snap-tab, it doesn't do much in the way of securing items. I find this to be a great place to store my phone, a pen or 2, & other items of that nature that I want to quickly access frequently.
Inside, there is an open pocket on each side, approximately the same size as the tabbed pocket outside. On one of these pockets is a section to hold 2 cards such as ID/credit or debit card/ membership/loyalty &/or business cards. I use this to hold my most frequently accessed membership/loyalty cards that don't have a keychain tab option. The main area inside is sizable, able to hold a Kindle Fire & a full sized wallet (the kind that allows your bills to lie flat rather than having to fold them), amongst other things.
I consider this a medium sized purse (coming from an 'It girl' purse) which still allows me to carry all my day-to-day needs & wants.
I highly recommend!

I had originally bought another reversible ring from this place and it was a teardrop ring with the White topaz on one side and the Alexandrite on the other side.

The disappointment comes into play with the size of the text & design (I‚Äôm pretty sure they were engraved by someone who normally engraves names on a grain of rice), and secondly, the jump rings for the tags & charms lost their brass color within two weeks. This part is actually okay with me, but for others that are thinking they are brass, or will stay that color‚Ä¶..they wont.
The dinosaur design was the hardest to see, and had room to be larger in size. The heart design was the same situation. The best sized design was the sun, and it was paired with the largest font of the three tags.

text: I got these in the Sterling Silver "Blue Cubic Zirconia" color & wow, the blue color of them is just outstanding & unique! It's a bright & sparkly blue that's sure to get noticed & they're just the right size for my second earring hole. They come in a nice gift box as well & they also come with clear rubber backings, if you prefer to use those instead of their sterling silver backings. I haven't worn them yet, but I shouldn't have any issues with wearing them. I usually wear sterling silver earrings in my ears for months at a time, through showering & sleeping, with no problems until they finally start to tarnish & then I'll put in a different pair. I have to say that the beautiful blue hue of these are probably going to be my favorite set of stud earrings so far! :)

title: *Pretty & sparkly sterling silver amethyst earrings!*
text:
I got these in the Sterling Silver purple "Amethyst" color & they look like a light purple/lavender sort of color when you're holding the earrings in your hand, but when you put them in your ear, they're a deeper, richer, darker shade of purple when you're wearing them, which makes them look like the elegant purple shade of "royalty." :)

They're a nice size for my first earring hole (& I got sterling silver stud earrings in a smaller size from this same company "Adita Gold," in their "Blue Cubic Zirconia" color for my second earring hole & that blue is a very beautiful, bright, vibrant, & sparkly blue!) So I'm pleased with both sets of earrings I've received from this company. Both came in nice gift boxes & with clear rubber backings if you prefer to use those instead of the regular backings they come with.

I haven't worn either set of earrings yet, but I've never had an issue with wearing sterling silver earrings & I leave them in for long periods of time with no issues & I sleep/shower in them as well. So I'm sure these will work out great! They're a lovely gift item to give someone & they seem like quality earrings. The colors of the stones aren't bland either...they seem more sparkly & "multi-faceted" in color than my other stud earrings are! :)

title: Hopeful and encouraging
text:
Jewelry that's encouraging, beautiful, and creatively made.

Waymaker Leather's leather and silver Bible verse-embossed bracelets are just a joy. This one is constructed of a lovely silver buckle and light brown Italian leather. The leather is 18" long and is designed to wrap twice around your wrist; if there's extra leather that you don't need you can just snip off the extra length with scissors. The leather is attached to the buckle on one end, and the other end tucks into the buckle after you've wrapped the bracelet around. It's easy to do one-handed.

The bracelet is tucked into a beautiful brown Waymaker Leather gift box which has their signature crowned lion behind a lamb. Inside, you'll find directions on how to customize fit for your own bracelet, a linen-y drawstring bag, the Bible verse printed on a card, and the bracelet itself.

This bracelet is the Hope bracelet. It has a wonderful Bible verse laser-embossed on it: "May the God of all hope fill you with all joy and peace as you trust in him, so that you may overflow with hope by the power of the Holy Spirit." That's from Romans 15:13. What a perfect verse post-Covid, when I feel that we're all looking for a little hope!

I love this bracelet. The verse on hope is one that encourages me when I look at the bracelet. This can be worn alone or stacked with other bracelets. In any case, I believe it's one that will also encourage you.

title: a handmade gem
text:
I love the great outdoors coupled with a hand crafted glass for a well crafted beverage.
I don‚Äôt believe you could get anything better than Black Lantern‚Äôs company making beautiful designs on a simple, sturdy short glass.
Their trees design is detailed, I do wish it encircled the full glass, but it‚Äôs still very neat. This particular design seems to be a nice representation of their location (Colorado mountains) and mentality of a love for the outdoors and sustainability.
Their logos encourage you to, ‚Äúfind your trail‚Äù and enjoy it with one of their rocks glasses while being mindful not to destroy it.
I would highly recommend any of their ornate, nature inspired glasses. There is a wide variety to choose from, and all of the designs could easily be appreciated by anyone who has a love for the great outdoors and a solid drink in a unique glass.

title: a wonderful gift and hand made gem
text:
A friend of mine loves nothing more than the great outdoors and playing his guitar. That‚Äôs a lie, he also loves a well crafted beverage. This Black Lantern glass ware set could not be a more perfect gift.
The glasses are solid and simple. The design is unique and detailed. I do wish the image wrapped fully around the glass.
Nevertheless, these glasses with a tree/sky line shaped into a guitar is so neat.
Anyone with a love for music and nature will really appreciate this set. Not to mention, supporting a small business with hand made merchandise that is well crafted and unique is always a win win. Black Lantern has a large variety of glassware to choose from, so finding a gift for someone special is a breeze. I would highly recommend.

title: Smells amazing!
text:
I've used the Luxe Organix Tea Tree shampoo/Conditioner twice now. I have long, fine, straight, color treated/highlighted hair.
Here are the pros/cons:

Pros:
1-Smells amazing and the scent while not over powering, lasts for days. Slight vanilla scent. I usually shampoo 2x per week.
2- Leaves my hair feeling very soft.
3- A little goes a long way. I use about an 3/4 of an ounce of shampoo and maybe 1.5 of conditioner per use.
4- Great organic ingredients

Cons:
1- Does not provide great detangling. I need to comb through after conditioning before rinsing, and it is difficult.
2- Small bottles
3- High price in my opinion
4- Even though my hair feels soft, the ends are a little frizzy.

And not really the products fault....
Some ingredient in it makes my cat nuts and he attacks my head and wants to chew on my hair. He has never done this before. It's really pretty funny.

I hope you found this review helpful

title: Elegantly Simple
text:
These jade earrings are a nice, smaller size for an understated look. They are easy to wear and are nice and lightweight. They provided a couple of different earring back options, which is always nice so you can use the set you prefer. The color of the stones in my earrings were a light green and offer a nice pop of color to any outfit. I love that they are nickel free and my ears have not experienced any irritation.

The earrings arrived in a little gift box. I really struggled to get the box open and was ready to cut through the clear top. The wooden hinge on the box was taped shut, as was the clasp. You have to cut the tape open and then pull hard to get this to open. If you are gifting these to someone who is older or lacks hand strength, you might want to open it ahead of time so that they can open and enjoy their gift. These earrings do make a great gift for both old and young alike. The size and design is appropriate for just about anyone and the price is a great deal!

The card and packaging add a nice touch to it, though they are very specific. Having a blank reason card option would be nice to let people fill out the reason field with anything. It seems like it would make the product line easier to manage and broaden the demographic scope as well.

A good value overall and definitely recommend.

title: I love the pendant, but confusing title, fluctuating price, and confusing pictures
text:
I am giving this 5 stars for the pendant itself. Never thought I would "feel" something when holding a rock, but somehow, I feel peaceful when holding this stone.

I think they are trying to say that it is similar to moldavite in that they're both tektites. But since it's NOT moldavite, it's confusing that they put that in the title, or product name.

The pictures are confusing because they show it in front of a flashlight and if you don't realize that, you might be disappointed to get a rock that's kind of boring-looking. Also, in one picture, the rocks are on a wooden hand... that's not meant to be for scale, apparently. The rock is nowhere near that size compared to an adult hand.

I've seen the pricing on this fluctuate wildly, so I can't say whether it's a good value or not, because of the fluctuations. Best to compare. I can tell you, though, that mine arrived in good shape, no damage... and like I said before, I think I feel something when holding it. I actually own moldavite and other gemstones and tektites, just because I'm a collector since I was a kid, but this is the first time I feel something when holding a stone. It doesn't seem to do anything when I wear it around my neck, but when I hold it, I feel like it has a calming energy... I don't know, just the feeling I get!

I almost forgot to mention that it also came with a free gift, a natural stone pendant. That was also a nice surprise.
