text: [[VIDEOID:d36b3deec57d5b1073e2f5836edf8eca]] The zircons on these earrings remind me a little drops of water on a flower after it rains. That is, they‚Äôre not the super sparkly kind of CZ but they are very pretty in and of themselves. I was kind of hoping that the flat earring backs would work with some of my screwback earrings so that I could wear my screw back earrings to bed and not worry about them poking me all night, but it seems that these earring backs only work with the earrings that they come with. It is nice that they come with an extra earring back in case you lose one. I‚Äôll also note that the rough threaded part of the post is only at the very tip, which is covered by the earring back when it screwed on, so if you‚Äôre going to wear these, you don‚Äôt have to worry about getting irritation from having a screw threads moving around in your ear hole! These are great if you have a lot of piercings and you can‚Äôt be bothered to remove all of your earrings every night; they‚Äôre very comfortable to sleep on.

title: Looks great!
text:
Back when I was in junior high and high school, I would probably make around a dozen of these for people every week, with whatever colors that they wanted. I still remember how to make them, but I just don't have the time or patience anymore!
So I saw these and thought that it would be neat to wear again. I really love the different colors and designs that comes with this. You get 5 bracelets total, with 4 being the fabric ones and 1 being a black, elastic beaded bracelet. You get a black with white, white with black, pink with purple/blue, and purple/blue with pink.
I especially love the black and white ones. I was actually more excited to put them on than I thought I would be! However, I do have a small issue with them.
If you look at the pictures I put up, even though I have the bracelet as tight as it will go, it is still quite big and very easily gets down to the halfway part of my hand after wearing it for less than an hour. I'm afraid that if I were to wear it longer and do the usual things I do every day it would end up getting loosened and fall off without me knowing it.
The way they are kept tied is with a specific style of knot that has 2 strings on each side. When you put a finger on the knot and pull on one of the strings, it will loosen on on side. By doing this with the other string it loosens on the other side. I really love this style to keep it on because it's really easy to take it on and off, but because I own a few bracelets with the same mechanic, I know that throughout the day, they tend to loosen up a little bit by the end of the day. It's because of that, that I know that these being as big as they are when as tight as they can be, they will more than likely get loosened through the day and that is not good.
I am a woman in her early 40s and wear a dress size 12/14. So if these are loose on my wrists, then I highly suspect that they will be even more loose on someone younger than me. Easily.
Does that mean I wouldn't recommend getting them?? No, not necessarily. I just wanted to bring this to everyone's attention so they know to be aware so they can keep an eye on it so it doesn't accidentally slip off. They are still really pretty and cool looking bracelets that would be good for a gift for your kids, or for them to have as gifts for their friends. I wish I could give advice on how to shorten it if needed, but I can't make the knot like this has. Wish I could because it's really cool and I like that a lot of bracelets have this now. Just be careful when wearing it is all I'm saying. They are well worth getting and are a fantastic bargain for how many you get.

text:

It's well made, with soldered rings so it won't break apart and get lost easily. I wear a 6.5" bracelet and this fits me perfectly without needing to use the extender. I thought the extender chain might get wrapped around and tangled up with the bracelet, but it doesn't. It's not so long that it gets in the way, and the butterfly is a cute accent.

The only reason it's not getting five stars is that the clasp is marked 925, so should be sterling silver, as advertised, but it reacts very strongly to a magnet. The bracelet itself doesn't react to the magnet, but this makes me question what it's actually made of. Rhodium plating with nickel underneath can react slightly to a magnet, so maybe that's why the clasp reacts - but then I'd think the rest of the bracelet would react also, since it's also supposed to be rhodium plated. Just not sure about the authenticity of the 925 mark, but I do love the bracelet style.

text:
I loooooove my necklace!! I am a sucker for dainty jewelry and in addition, i am crazy for natural stones.. this necklace is perfect for my taste and is absolutely beautiful!

The necklace is, as mentioned, very dainty. I would definitely look carefully at the pictures provided for the correct scale of the actual size as it‚Äôs represented accurately in the pictures. Not everyone loves dainty jewelry so if you‚Äôre not a fan, maybe pass it by, though, the necklace is so beautiful, it‚Äôs worth taking the chance! I absolutely love how simple but classy it is!

In addition it seems to be made very well! The product pictures, and my pictures, barely illustrate how sparkly the beads and chain really are. The chain is smooth, unlike typical link chains, and has a satin like look that‚Äôs so pretty! The beads are beautiful.. they really sparkle! I got the black spinel and despite being a dark, solid color, they still sparkle! The beads also have a ‚Äúrough‚Äù non polished look that adds a bit of rustic with the pretty elegance.

There is an extension link on the chain so this can be worn at several lengths. I like having that option. Also it came beautifully packaged and entirely gift ready. It comes with a sweet message and a small polishing cloth as a nice bonus! All packed safely and professionally in a nice box.

Overall i am thrilled!! I got this from the handmade section so, if it‚Äôs indeed handmade, bravo to the crafter for such beautiful work! I definitely recommend the necklace.. it would be perfect for anyone and/or any occasion.. All for a very fair price!

title: Took my breath away.
text:
I am a rock and crystal enthusiast. Here is my two cents.

When I saw this listing, I pounced, since I lost my beloved larimar necklace from Moab.
The order did not disappoint. This larimar is authentic-looking and simply gorgeous.
If I was being picky, though, I would say that these stones were intentionally packaged; They were placed in the bag in the order of saturation of color. Five of them have the traditional translucent, electric blue rippling Larimar appearance‚Äîthe other five look a little chalk-like, and I would have difficulty even guessing they were larimar right off the bat‚Äî However, I can tell they are real, because I have learned that authentic larimar will have white neuron-like striations on it, which of these rocks do have, though they are a pale blue, rather than the vivid color of the ‚Äúprettier‚Äù ones.

title: Beautiful glass with delicate silver wire wrap
text: This is a beautiful piece of green sea glass that's delicately wrapped with silver wire. It's a very nice presentation. They've also added a fake pearl charm, and a small silver mermaid charm on the chain to keep the theme going. I like the glass without the other charms, but for a young girl they would be perfect. To me it detracts from the elegance of the glass, but it's easy to separate the parts with some needle nose pliers. The backside of the glass has a similar wrapping, just not the spiral at the bottom, so it looks good on both sides. The glass looks different in every picture, but the color is a medium green, not light nor dark green. The chain is cheap but works, though I find it very difficult to close by myself. My main love is the sea glass and it's so lovely that I can handle the rest. It's a good price for this necklace and any water-loving young girl would love this. title: Nice sized Moonstone Bracelet!!
text:
I ordered this to give to my daughter because moonstone is one of her June birthstones!
This is a nice moonstone bracelet. I like the larger size beads its made with.
It does have the blue flash/sheen, you just have to catch the light right and understand that low, mid or higher quality moonstone are each different as a whole.
Not every Bead of this shows the blue sheen look, most have a duller-cloudy look to them. But again different quality moonstones may/may not have a blue sheen look to them at all whatsoever.
This did come with extra elastic string along with two extra beads. I will say that I personally liked the Two Extra moonstone beads a lil better and wished that the entire bracelet looked them.
But it's ok, it's still a nice moonstone bracelet.
It didn't include any information about being natural moonstone, no helpful information card of how to clean or take care of it. No cleaning or any instructions at all.
Overall all I Like it,
I'd reorder it again if need be. Biggest thing to understand is; that not all moonstone is going to look the same.
Some are of higher quality, some are opaque, transparent & have great light refraction, some have an amazing & wonderful blue flash/sheen look and some don't have it at all.
There are natural, pink/peach, grey/black or even higher quality that are nearly completely transparent,clear, or see through moonstones that most people (or myself specifically speaking) wish they had or could afford LoL!
Some people may not like this perticular bracelet or it's quality/colouration. Some people may say this doesn't meet their expectations at all whatsoever. And some will find it to be just fine!
The only thing I'd adjust is;
that maybe whomever hand selects the semiprecious gem-stone crystal beads for use for jewelry, that they'd select better quality ones such as the two extra moonstone beads this bracelet came with, keep the ones that show good light refraction and add other similar ones as they're making their jewelry.
On that note; this pretty much sums up my personal opinions & thoughts on this perticular item. I'd like to say; Thank U for taking two time to read through this review.
I hope it and the photos I added are all helpful to others in one way or another üòä
HAVE AN AWESOME Day üòä

title: Love this
text:
I am a bit confused about why this product is called a serum, when in all actuality, it is very much a facial oil and not a serum. I am hoping it was a miscommunication or something like that.
Anyway - aside from the product being misnamed, I am still really happy with it. First thing I noticed immediately when it was delivered (with the box of the product already opened up) was the very pleasant scent that it has!! It's not strong, yet is very nice and actually gives me flashbacks of events in my past. The reason for that is because the scent, to me anyways, reminds me of every time I was ever staying in a hotel. You know how it seems like all of the soaps and shampoo and stuff that you find/use at a hotel have a very similar scent? Well, that's exactly what this facial oil smells like to me!! I had my daughter smell it, but she didn't agree with me on this, so I guess it's open for debate. Lol.
I have been using this product every other night for around a month now. I noticed that my face is a lot softer, I can see some slight improvement in the fine lines on my forehead, and especially on my laugh lines. To be quite honest, I am quite impressed with this!! I really wasn't sure if I would see any changes at all, mainly because a lot of stuff on the market today makes promises and fail to live up to them. This one however, after a month, is actually keeping it's promise!!
So if you are interested in trying out something new to help your face feel softer and improve the fine lines and wrinkles, then I highly recommend this to you or anyone you know. I've been trying to find something to do these things that won't end up breaking the bank, and I am not only impressed with the product, but it's a very good deal too!! Will definitely be getting some more when this is empty!!

When I tried to adjust it, it bent very quickly and easily to the point I thought it might break and it's now slightly out of shape. It seems that you can only adjust it a tiny bit before it bends out of shape. I didn't use much force at all. I have it set to the size I want for a specific finger and will not be adjusting it anymore as I am afraid it will break. So yes it's pretty but it seems quite fragile...... For this reason I'm not sure it's worth the price.....I would recommend not even adjusting it if you can help it.....

title: Sweet and petite gift for mom
text: I bought this necklace for my grandsons to present to their mom on Mother's Day.  It is very petite (dainty) as described.  The little bird engraved on the front is so small that it is a bit hard to make out just what it is.  Although this is described as a "locket", the two halves of the sphere do not fit together or stay closed as one might expect.  The little eggs and engraving of the nest on the inside are really very sweet, as is the card with the sentimental poem.  Also nice is the explanation of the Amazonite from which the tiny eggs are made.  The 16" chain would be short on many adults, but there is a 2" extension option which will make it fit on almost everyone.  I am sure that my daughter will like this necklace because it will come from her boys.

title: So unique!
text:
I squealed when I took these out of the package. Look, you're either going to think these earrings are ridiculous or the most amazing thing you've ever seen, and you can guess which side I'm on.

The rhinestones on the parrots are perfectly placed to add a nice amount of sparkle without being too overwhelmingly gaudy. I also love that the hoops that the parrot perch connects to are huggies. They seem to clip together fine though it does seem like they're a bit softer than I like so they may deform in the future, but at this low price point it's hard to complain. Despite their size, they're not particularly heavy, nor have I broken out from wearing them yet.

If you're yearning to be in the tiki tiki tiki tiki tiki room with some feathery friends, these are the perfect earrings!

title: Comfortable Classic Topaz Solitaire Necklace
text: [[VIDEOID:b509bc625327485142d0323de0d4228d]] I have really been appreciating this sterling silver and topaz necklace! First of all, it is constructed of genuine sterling silver! The pendant and necklace are both properly stamped as well! The lobster clasp is sturdy and easy to operate. I can take this on and off by myself, with no further assistance. I like the topaz setting a lot, especially how it is on a hinge! This allows it to twinkle a little bit more than the standard, run-of-the-mill solitaire pendant setting! If I could change one thing, it would be the fact that you can not remove the pendant from the necklace. I have added other, additional charms on the necklace with the topaz. The necklace chain is definitely strong and sturdy. All in all, this is a totally decent deal for a beautiful sterling necklace! I recommend it!

title: Might be Too Lightweight
text: These are really pretty earrings. The mother of pearl is so light and polished it looks like resin. I put these on to try and they felt great, like I wasn't even wearing earrings - except for the part where the back of the earring kept getting caught in my long hair and getting twisted. By the time I went to take these out, the back of one earring had twisted really terribly and it was weird to take it out because it wasn't smooth at all. I was able to push the back into shape, but now I'm worried about wearing these and getting bumped weirdly so that it squashes the back and makes taking the earring off difficult. I'll definitely wear these with caution moving forward.

It doesn't feel like the band will break after you readjust the size a couple times! The butterflies' cubic zirconia stones are set perfectly. This arrived free of any issues or imperfections. It's comfortable to wear on its own, as well as stacked and combined with other rings! I think this is adorable, and totally recommend it!

title: Works Fast
text: I have a dry spot on one of my elbows that I have been using lotion on daily to try to get rid of for months and it never went away. This only took one application and it is so much better! I love supporting companies like this. Ones that use organic ingredients, are hand made and made in the USA. So when I see complaints about the price I feel the need to point out that with every dollar you spend you are making a choice, placing a vote for the kind of world you want, the kind of products you want. Do you want chemically laden, cheap products from China? Or do you want to support natural, hand made products and the hard working Americans that make them? For me, the answer is easy. I will buy from this company again and I will buy this product again.

title: Nice Looking Bracelet, Great Pressentation
text: This bracelet comes in a handsome black gift box with gold print. Inside there is a gray felt pouch with a snap closure that contains the bracelet. There are two brown cards inside the box as well. One explains the triple protection properties of the silver sheen obsidian, the tiger's eye, and the hematite. The second card explains the maintenance and care of the bracelet. As others have mentioned, this bracelet is not adjustable, so measure carefully and make sure you order the right size. I am impressed with both the looks of the bracelet and the presentation, from the elegant looking gift box to the gift pouch inside the box. This bracelet is my gift to myself, but it would also make a very nice gift for others.

title: Really Works, and Works Well
text: This tube of StinkBalm looks like chapstick and smells like exactly what it is, menthol and a blend of other essential oils. It works like a champ. In my kitchen I have a large container with a screw-on lid that I use for organic kitchen waste until it's full enough to carry out to my compost bin outside. After the container gets to about the halfway point, it starts smelling pretty ripe when I take the lid off. I tried this balm underneath my nostrils today, and all I could smell was the balm and not a bit of the odor from the container. I deem that an outstanding success. The scent of the balm lingered for quite a while, so had I been cooking something and had to use the container repeatedly for the food scraps, I still would have been in great shape. This is an excellent product, and I'm so glad I ordered it.

title: Larger beads than expected, but still fits great and is made well.
text:
This bracelet is a little bit larger than I normally wear, but it is well made and fits well.

The stones almost look like they are slightly green - I don't know if black obsidian is meant to have a hint of green or not, or if it's because the string holding it together is dark green. The carved bead in the center is definitely hard to make out what it's depicting - the dark color doesn't show the detail.

It was easy to put on (pull it loose to make the bracelet larger, slide on, and then pull the strings to tighten with one hand and one mouth (or get a friend to help). It's a nice addition to jewelry, but probably not one I'll wear as often just because of the size and weight of the stones. I'm very picky with my jewelry and I usually like to forget that I'm wearing it.

title: The "moon" charm is clever - little imperfections look like moon craters!
text: I like this bracelet - it's lightweight and the "moon" bead is interesting. It's larger but light because of the type of rock (I think lava rock), and it has little moon-like pockmarks which adds character. The only real  complaint I have is that the strings on the back that you use to loosen/tighten the bracelet are too long when tightened. I'm likely going to cut them to shorten it, so it doesn't get caught in everything when I'm wearing it.

title: This bracelet was a bit tight in widening to wear, but loosened up after several tries
text:
I've not seen white stones like this before, and I admit when I first felt and looked at these, I thought it was plastic. I'm still not 100% positive, but there are no telltale plastic marks on the beads, so I am sure it's just very well polished stone that has a plastic-like feel.

I like that the bracelet is lightweight, and the marbling gives it character that is more interesting than just plain white beads would be. The strings to tighten the bracelet are a bit too long - and being white means that they will get dirty a lot more quickly. I'll have to cut it down before that happens!

title: Beautiful Gem Bracelets!
text:
This pair of gemstone bracelets comes in a nice gift box. The two bracelets are tied together by a tag that you'll need to cut off to separate the bracelets. There are two types of bracelets that are slightly different. Both have yellow tiger eye. One has polished obsidian and polished hematite. The other has unpolished obsidian and lava rock. The lava rock is interesting because it has pores and texture. The beads look great and the tiger eye has plenty of shine and luster. The polish on the hematite and obsidian is also very shiny.

The bracelets are adjusted by pulling two drawstrings that are friction fit by a series of weaves. The drawstrings have a small bead at each end so you have something to grip. They are easy to fit to your wrist and don't loosen while wearing them. The cord that holds it together is synthetic and tough.

I love the way these bracelets look and feel!

title: Not Unisex sizing
text:
Absolutely purchase this T shirt if you are a size 00. It is darling, to be sure. But Unisex sizing? No way. An american Unisex small has always been my go to size. Not fitted, but not super loose. Enough room to fit the girls in without having them scream at you, you know?
I ordered a unisex Small, and I'm quite sure it is for a 12 year old boy. Some baseball moms love to have their ta-tas do the talking, I'm not that mom. Quietly melting into the background is more my style. This shirt will have any mom being the center of attention, to be sure. Not only will your boobies look enormous, as this cheap fabric is stretched to it's breaking point, you get the added benefit of a crop top, so when you sit on those bleachers, your entire crack will be skillfully displayed to all of the curious on-lookers in the seats above you.

Basically. Order 3 sizes up. Or better yet, maybe don't order at all. There are no exchanges, and no prime shipping. There are plenty of other shirts just like this with better prices, better customer service and free shipping.
